fields.name: Create Jira tickets
fields.description: Business analyst creates Jira tickets for reference data changes and integration investigation.

fields.name: Close the reference data change Jira ticket
Verify reference data changes
fields.description: Ensure reference data has been updated according to the data requirements.

fields.name: Refine the data requirements
fields.description: Business analyst refines the data requirements on the Confluence template.

fields.name: Prioritize reference data updates
fields.description: Reference data team prioritizes the Jira tickets.

fields.name: Accept Jira tickets
fields.description: Change Jira ticket status to "Selected for development".

fields.name: Fill data specification template
fields.description:
Business analyst creates and fills the initial information in the data specification template in Confluence.

The status of data specification template is DRAFT.

fields.name: Collect data requirements
fields.description:
Business analyst collects the data requirements from business stakeholders.

Business analyst collects reference data values and translations.

fields.name: Prioritize source integration analysis
fields.description: Source integration team prioritizes the Jira tickets.

fields.name: Make the change to reference data
fields.description: Create new reference data code sets and make the necessary changes to the existing ones.

fields.name: Prioritize data requirement
fields.description:
Business stakeholder gives priorities for the various data.

Information architect gives input about overall situation of logical data model development.

Upper management gives project priorities.

DTF decides the urgency and business impact of the data requirement based on these inputs. Priority is calculated based on the urgency and business impact and recorded on the template by DTF.

fields.name: Make roadmap for data requirements
fields.description:
Ask for work estimates and timeline from teams. Reference data team can estimate the work related to the reference data, and integration team Scrum Masters may estimate how much work is needed in the analysis face and when resources are available.

Typically some data requirements have higher priority than others. Prioritize data requirements, bundle data requirements into releases. Make a roadmap of the releases.

fields.name: Ensure data requirements are sufficiently defined
fields.description: Before proceeding, information architect ensures that the data requirements are sufficiently defined for logical model and data source definition.

fields.name: Invetisgate source system data model against the data requirements
fields.description: Source system experts investigate source system data model against the data requirements and make initial work estimates based on the work required.

fields.name: Get approval, funding and priority for roadmap
fields.description: Business stakeholder takes the roadmap to B2B or B2C program for approval to analysis phase, and priority with regards to other projects.

fields.name: Approve the data specification
fields.description: Change the status of data specification template to DONE.

fields.name: Close the source system integration Jira ticket
Choose context
fields.description: Information architect decides the context for the data requirement based on the input from the business analyst. Context is recorded into the data specification template.

fields.name: Plan the work
fields.description:
Sprint Planning for source integration team for participation in the analysis phase.

Sprint Planning for reference data team for implementing the reference data.

fields.name: Implementation and time capacity planning
fields.description: Capacity and time line planning for the analysis phase, synchronize with other projects
